<section id="problem-statement" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <!-- Section Title -->
    <h2 class="section-heading reveal">
      Sensor-to-Decision Bottleneck in Agentic Autonomy
    </h2>

    <!-- Intro Paragraph -->
    <div class="prose reveal">
      <p>
        Agentic AI robots increasingly couple high-rate multimodal sensing with learned perception and foundation-model reasoning, yet deployment failures often arise from a <strong>sensor-to-decision bottleneck</strong>, not weak models. Systems may report strong per-frame accuracy and low latency, but these metrics fail unless predictions are grounded in <strong>fresh, decision-time evidence</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Highlight Box (Converted from your abstract) -->
    <div class="problem-highlights reveal">
      <p>Key system-level limitations:</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">

        <!-- Item 1 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <span class="highlight-number">⚠️</span>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Stale Decision Inputs</h4>
            <p>Queueing delays force decisions on outdated sensor evidence despite high model accuracy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 2 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <span class="highlight-number">💾</span>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Low-Value Data Overload</h4>
            <p>Redundant and vibration-amplified streams saturate onboard pipelines and waste compute.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 3 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <span class="highlight-number">⚡</span>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Delayed Informative Evidence</h4>
            <p>High-value frames arrive too late, degrading real-time decision reliability.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Contribution / Bridge -->
    <div class="prose reveal">
      <p>
        <strong>SenseGuard</strong> addresses this gap by treating robustness as a <strong>decision-time freshness objective</strong>. It combines an online adaptive filtering policy with an offline, model-centric data curation strategy to ensure timely perception and efficient continual improvement.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- Research Questions Section -->
<section id="research-questions" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Research Questions</h2>

    <div class="research-questions-box reveal">

      <!-- RQ1 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">1</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <p>
            <strong>RQ₁ (Online Autonomy):</strong><br/>
            How can we maximize <strong>decision-time data freshness</strong> so fast onboard models remain effective under limited compute?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RQ2 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">2</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <p>
            <strong>RQ₂ (Offline Improvement):</strong><br/>
            What <strong>minimal yet sufficient multimodal data</strong> should be retained to accelerate model improvement and robustness?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

